The HD 86950 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 86950 is a star with 1.66 times the mass of the Sun, and 8.8 times its radius. It is located 684.40 light years away from the solar system.

HD 86950 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 86950 system


HD 86950 b

HD 86950 b was discovered by the Multiple Observatories observatory, in 2017-02, using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 2.72 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 86950 b is 1144.800 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 86950 b is 13.000 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 86950 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
